10
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:25,740
Now, you remember, children,
how I told you last Sunday...

11
00:01:25,820 --> 00:01:29,140
about the good Lord going up into the
mountain and talking to the people...

12
00:01:29,260 --> 00:01:33,060
and how He said, "Blessed are the pure
in heart, for they shall see God"...

13
00:01:33,140 --> 00:01:36,580
and how He said that King Solomon
in all his glory...

14
00:01:36,660 --> 00:01:39,420
was not as beautiful
as the lilies of the field?

15
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:43,060
And I know you won't forget,
"Judge not lest ye be judged"...

16
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:45,180
because I explained that to you.

17
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,780
And then the Good Lord
went on to say...

18
00:01:48,860 --> 00:01:51,660
"Beware of false prophets...

19
00:01:51,740 --> 00:01:54,460
which come to you
in sheep's clothing...

20
00:01:54,580 --> 00:01:57,740
but inwardly
they are ravening wolves.

21
00:01:57,860 --> 00:02:00,660
Ye shall know them
by their fruits."

22
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,700
Five, ten, fifteen, twenty,
twenty-five, thirty, thirty-five...

23
00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:05,260
forty, forty-five, fifty, fifty-five,
sixty, sixty-five, seventy...

24
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:08,500
seventy-five, eighty, eighty-five,
ninety, ninety-five, one hundred!

25
00:02:08,620 --> 00:02:10,700
Here I come, ready or not!

26
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:14,380
What's wrong?

27
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,500
Hey! Hey!

28
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:29,260
"A good tree cannot
bring forth evil fruit.

29
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:32,780
Neither can a corrupt tree
bring forth good fruit.

30
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:36,340
Wherefore, by their fruits,
ye shall know them."

31
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,900
Well, now, what's it to be, Lord?

32
00:02:42,020 --> 00:02:44,180
Another widow?

33
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,860
How many has it been? Six?

34
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:50,860
Twelve? I disremember.

35
00:02:54,620 --> 00:02:57,900
You say the word, Lord,
I'm on my way.

36
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:08,980
You always send me money
to go forth and preach Your Word.

37
00:03:10,460 --> 00:03:14,340
A widow with a little wad of bills
hid away in a sugar bowl.

38
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:27,180
Lord, I am tired.

39
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:30,940
Sometimes I wonder
if You really understand, Lord.

40
00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:35,740
Not that you mind the killings.
Your book is full of killings.

41
00:03:37,540 --> 00:03:39,660
But there are things
You do hate, Lord.

42
00:03:39,780 --> 00:03:43,180
Perfume-smelling things,
lacy things...

43
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,740
things with curly hair.

44
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:31,820
There are too many of them.
You can't kill a world.

45
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:36,700
You driving a touring car
with a Moundsville license?

46
00:04:36,820 --> 00:04:39,340
Harry Powell, for the theft
of that touring car...

47
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:42,380
