01:04:28,380 --> 01:04:30,540
You two youngsters get up
to me this instant.

727
01:04:31,980 --> 01:04:34,900
Get on up to my house!
Mind me, now!

728
01:04:35,020 --> 01:04:36,900
I'll get me a switch.

729
01:04:50,860 --> 01:04:52,580
- Don't you hurt her!
- Hurt her, nothing.

730
01:04:52,660 --> 01:04:54,100
Wash her's more like it.

731
01:04:54,220 --> 01:04:59,180
- Ruby! Clary! Mary!
- Yes, Miss Cooper?

732
01:04:59,260 --> 01:05:01,900
Bring your baskets.

733
01:05:05,780 --> 01:05:07,660
Nicely picked, Clary.

734
01:05:07,740 --> 01:05:10,300
Mary, put the big ones on top.

735
01:05:10,380 --> 01:05:12,500
Ruby, most of them ain't fit
to go to market.

736
01:05:12,620 --> 01:05:15,660
Well, put your baskets down.
Ruby, run to the house...

737
01:05:15,780 --> 01:05:18,100
and f etch the tub
and put it by the pump.

738
01:05:18,220 --> 01:05:21,220
Clary, Mary, run up and f etch
a bar of laundry soap.

739
01:05:21,300 --> 01:05:23,780
- Yes, Miss Cooper.
- And a scrub brush.

740
01:05:23,900 --> 01:05:25,940
Come on up to the house, children.

741
01:05:27,980 --> 01:05:30,740
Gracious, if you ain't
a sight to beat all.

742
01:05:30,860 --> 01:05:32,660
Where are you from?

743
01:05:33,860 --> 01:05:35,260
Where are your folks?

744
01:05:35,340 --> 01:05:37,460
Come on. Speak up, now.

745
01:05:39,860 --> 01:05:42,540
Gracious, so I've got
two more mouths to f eed.

746
01:06:08,900 --> 01:06:11,020
Howdy, Miss Cooper.
What happened to our milk supply?

747
01:06:11,140 --> 01:06:12,860
Price of milk what it is,
not on your lif e.

748
01:06:12,940 --> 01:06:15,340
Do better makin' butter with the cream.
Sell it retail.

749
01:06:15,460 --> 01:06:17,700
Make smearcase for the children.
Feed what's left to my hogs.

750
01:06:18,860 --> 01:06:21,180
- She talks to herself.
- All the time.

751
01:06:21,260 --> 01:06:23,420
- Your ma's funny.
- She ain't our ma.

752
01:06:23,500 --> 01:06:26,220
- We just live at her house.
- Where are your folks?

753
01:06:26,340 --> 01:06:29,220
- Someplace.
- My daddy's in Detroit.

754
01:06:34,940 --> 01:06:38,340
Good morning, Miss Cooper. Guess what?
I'm savin' to buy you a charm bracelet.

755
01:06:38,460 --> 01:06:42,300
Never mind the talk. Don't forget your
visit Sunday. Come to church with us.

756
01:06:44,340 --> 01:06:46,740
See you Sunday, love.

757
01:06:46,860 --> 01:06:49,300
Take your baskets in, children.

758
01:06:49,420 --> 01:06:51,580
Reminiscent fools.

759
01:06:51,660 --> 01:06:52,980
All of 'em.

760
01:06:54,380 --> 01:06:55,660
Look there.

761
01:06:56,780 --> 01:06:59,580
She'll be losing her mind
to a tricky mouth and a full moon...

762
01:06:59,660 --> 01:07:03,140
and like as not,
I'll be saddled with the consequences.

763
01:07:03,980 --> 01:07:05,540
Here's what you owe me.

764
01:07:07,180 --> 01:07:09,260
One, two, three, four, five.

765
01:07:09,340 --> 01:07:11,420
Where's the other basket?
Where's Ruby?

766
01:07:11,500 --> 01:07:14,900
- She went.
- John, you go find Ruby.

767
01:07:15,020 --> 01:07:16,900
Big Ruby's my bothersome girl.

768
01:07:17,020 --> 01:07:18,860
She can't gather eggs
without bustin' 'em...

769
01:07:18,940 --> 01:07:21,620
but she's got mother hands with
a young 'un, so what are you to say?

770
01:07:23,660 --> 01:07:25,420
How about tonight, Ruby?

771
01:07:25,540 --> 01:07:28,700
- What gives?
- The old lady's around.

772
01:07:28,780 --> 01:07:30,100
How about Thursday?

773
01:07:31,820 --> 01:07:35,180
The old gal thinks she comes in
for sewing lessons on Thursday.

774
01:07:35,300 --> 01:07:37,220
Miss Cooper wants you.

775
01:07:40,900 --> 01:07:43,060
And will you show me
your dolly, little lady?

776
01:07:44,740 --> 01:07:47,180
- I see you got two more to your brood.
- Yeah...

777
01:07:47,300 --> 01:07:50,220
- and ornerier than the rest.
- How's your own boy, Miss Cooper?

778
01:07:50,340 --> 01:07:52,940
Haven't heard from Ralph
since Christmas. Don't matter, though.

779
01:07:53,020 --> 01:07:55,580
I've got a new crop.

780
01:07:55,660 --> 01:07:58,940
I'm a strong tree
with branches for many birds.

781
01:07:59,020 --> 01:08:02,260
I'm good for something in this world,
and I know it too.

782
01:08:24,620 --> 01:08:26,260
Now, old Pharaoh...

783
01:08:26,380 --> 01:08:28,980
he was king of Egypt-land.

784
01:08:29,100 --> 01:08:30,940
And he had a daughter.

785
01:08:31,020 --> 01:08:35,140
And once upon a time...

786
01:08:35,220 --> 01:08:38,180
she was walkin' along by the riverbank,
and she seen somethin'...

787
01:08:38,260 --> 01:08:41,020
bumpin' and scrapin' along
on a sandbar...

788
01:08:41,100 --> 01:08:42,700
down under the willows.

789
01:08:42,820 --> 01:08:45,540
- And you know what it was, children?
- No.

790
01:08:45,620 --> 01:08:48,580
Now, it was a skiff
washed up on the bar.

791
01:08:49,660 --> 01:08:52,940
- And who do you reckon was in it?
- Pearl and John.

792
01:08:53,980 --> 01:08:56,700
Not this time.
There was only one young 'un--

793
01:08:56,780 --> 01:08:59,100
a little boy babe.

794
01:08:59,180 --> 01:09:02,060
- And you know who he was, children?
- No.

795
01:09:03,820 --> 01:09:06,740
It was Moses, a king of men.

796
01:09:06,860 --> 01:09:09,460
Moses, children.

797
01:09:09,580 --> 01:09:11,820
Now, off to bed with you.

798
01:09:11,900 --> 01:09:13,860
John, get me an apple.

799
01:09:30,380 --> 01:09:32,620
And get one for yourself too.

800
01:09:45,140 --> 01:09:47,180
John, where are your folks?

801
01:09:47,300 --> 01:09:49,660
- Dead.
- Dead.

802
01:09:51,260 --> 01:09:53,180
Where you from?

803
01:09:53,260 --> 01:09:54,820
Upriver.

804
01:09:56,500 --> 01:10:00,420
Didn't figure you'd rode that skiff
all the way up from Parkersburg.

805
01:10:13,900 --> 01:10:16,260
Tell me that story again.

806
01:10:16,340 --> 01:10:19,300
Story? What story, honey?

807
01:10:19,380 --> 01:10:21,020
About them kings.

808
01:10:21,100 --> 01:10:24,700
And the queen found down on the sandbar
that time in the skiff.

809
01:10:24,780 --> 01:10:29,100
Kings? Why, there was only
one king, honey.

810
01:10:29,220 --> 01:10:31,980
I mind you said there was two.

811
01:10:32,100 --> 01:10:35,340
Well, shoot, now.
Maybe there was.

812
01:10:36,380 --> 01:10:38,940
Yes, come to think of it,
there was two.

813
01:11:04,140 --> 01:11:06,860
Must be Thursday.
Here comes Ruby.

814
01:11:13,740 --> 01:11:15,540
Here I go.

815
01:11:21,780 --> 01:11:23,980
Why, you're Ruby,
ain't you, my child?

816
01:11:24,060 --> 01:11:26,140
- Can I have this?
- Surely.

817
01:11:26,220 --> 01:11:29,020
- I'd like to talk to you, my dear.
- Will you buy me an ice cream?

818
01:11:29,100 --> 01:11:30,900
- Of course.
- Watch out, Preacher.

819
01:11:31,020 --> 01:11:33,940
- Why, Preacher!
- Shut your dirty mouths.

820
01:11:44,940 --> 01:11:47,740
-Ain't I pretty?
-You're the prettiest thing I've seen...

821
01:11:47,820 --> 01:11:50,140
in all my wanderin'.

822
01:11:50,220 --> 01:11:52,780
Ain't nobody ever told you that, Ruby?

823
01:11:52,900 --> 01:11:54,660
No one never did.

824
01:11:55,540 --> 01:11:58,180
There's two new ones
out at your place, ain't there?

825
01:11:58,260 --> 01:11:59,620
Uh-huh.

826
01:12:00,540 --> 01:12:02,780
- What's their names?
- Pearl and John.

827
01:12:04,620 --> 01:12:08,300
- Is there a doll?
- Only they never let me play with it.

828
01:12:15,780 --> 01:12:18,780
Did you ever see such pretty eyes
in all your born days?

829
01:12:18,860 --> 01:12:21,940
- Don't let him get away, sugar.
- He ain't like you all.

830
01:12:22,060 --> 01:12:24,900
Next time I won't even ask him
to buy me an ice cream.

831
01:12:33,340 --> 01:12:35,180
I's been bad.

832
01:12:38,980 --> 01:12:40,940
Ruby, you didn't have money
to buy this.

833
01:12:41,060 --> 01:12:43,580
- You'll whip me.
- When did I ever?

834
01:12:43,660 --> 01:12:46,620
- This man at the drugstore, he gave--
- The drugstore?

835
01:12:48,260 --> 01:12:51,620
Miss Cooper, I never been
to sewing lessons all them times.

836
01:12:51,740 --> 01:12:54,100
What you been up to, Ruby?

837
01:12:54,220 --> 01:12:56,100
I've been out with men.

838
01:12:57,940 --> 01:12:59,300
Child.

839
01:13:03,740 --> 01:13:07,620
You were looking for love, Ruby,
in the only foolish way you knew how.

840
01:13:11,900 --> 01:13:14,220
We all need love, Ruby.

841
01:13:14,340 --> 01:13:16,740
I lost the love of my son.

842
01:13:16,860 --> 01:13:18,860
I found it with you all.

843
01:13:20,740 --> 01:13:23,820
You're gonna grow up to be
a strong, fine woman...

844
01:13:23,900 --> 01:13:26,060
and I'm gonna see that you do.

845
01:13:26,180 --> 01:13:30,460
The gentleman weren't like them. He just
give me a book and buy me ice cream.

846
01:13:30,540 --> 01:13:33,540
- Now, who was this?
- He didn't ask me for nothin'.

847
01:13:33,620 --> 01:13:37,220
- What did you talk about?
- Pearl and John.

848
01:13:37,300 --> 01:13:40,380
John and Pearl?
Is he their pap?

849
01:13:40,460 --> 01:13:43,140
I don't know.

850
01:13:43,220 --> 01:13:45,500
Wonder why he hasn't been
to the house.

851
01:14:02,940 --> 01:14:06,020
- Miss Cooper! Miss Cooper!
- What?

852
01:14:06,100 --> 01:14:08,380
The man! The man!

853
01:14:12,420 --> 01:14:14,100
Good mornin', ladies.

854
01:14:14,180 --> 01:14:17,780
- How do?
- Why, you're Miss Cooper, I take it.

855
01:14:17,900 --> 01:14:20,140
It's about that John
and that Pearl?

856
01:14:20,220 --> 01:14:22,260
Oh, them poor little lambs.

857
01:14:22,380 --> 01:14:24,700
To think I never hoped to see them
again in this world.

858
01:14:24,780 --> 01:14:27,340
Oh, dear madam,
if you was to know...

859
01:14:27,460 --> 01:14:31,980
what a crown of thorns I've borne
in my search for them strayed chicks.

860
01:14:32,100 --> 01:14:34,140
Ruby, go f etch them kids.

861
01:14:37,300 --> 01:14:40,260
Oh, madam, I see
you're looking at my hands.

862
01:14:40,340 --> 01:14:42,220
Would you like me
to tell you a story...

863
01:14:42,300 --> 01:14:44,620
of left hand and right hand,
the tale of good and evil?

864
01:14:44,700 --> 01:14:47,500
It was with this left hand that
old brother Cain struck the blow...

865
01:14:47,580 --> 01:14:50,100
- that laid his brother low.
- Them kids is yours?

866
01:14:50,220 --> 01:14:54,020
- My own flesh and blood.
- Where's your missus?

867
01:14:54,140 --> 01:14:58,540
She run off with a drummer
during prayer meeting.

868
01:14:58,660 --> 01:15:00,740
- Where's she at?
- Down the river somewheres.

869
01:15:00,820 --> 01:15:04,220
Parkersburg or Cincinnati--
one of them Sodoms of the Ohio River.

870
01:15:04,300 --> 01:15:06,300
She took them kids with her?

871
01:15:06,380 --> 01:15:08,820
Heaven only knows
what unholy sights and sounds...

872
01:15:08,940 --> 01:15:10,740
them innocent
little babes has heard...

873
01:15:10,860 --> 01:15:13,100
in the dens of perdition
where she dragged 'em.

874
01:15:13,220 --> 01:15:16,780
Right funny, ain't it, how they rode
all the way upriver in a ten-foot boat?

875
01:15:19,460 --> 01:15:22,860
- Are they well, Miss Cooper?
- A sight better than they was.

876
01:15:24,380 --> 01:15:28,020
Gracious, gracious, you are
a good woman, Miss Cooper.

877
01:15:28,140 --> 01:15:30,580
How you figurin' to raise
them two without a woman?

878
01:15:30,700 --> 01:15:32,860
The Lord will provide.

879
01:15:32,940 --> 01:15:34,500
The Lord is merciful.

880
01:15:34,620 --> 01:15:36,820
Oh, what a day this is.

881
01:15:36,940 --> 01:15:38,820
And there's little John.

882
01:15:38,900 --> 01:15:41,580
- What's wrong, John?
- Come to me, boy.

883
01:15:41,700 --> 01:15:44,340
- What's wrong, John?
- Didn't you hear me, boy?

884
01:15:44,460 --> 01:15:46,820
John, when your dad says come,
you should mind him.

885
01:15:46,940 --> 01:15:48,780
He ain't my dad.

886
01:15:51,980 --> 01:15:54,980
No, and he ain't
no preacher, neither.

887
01:16:02,220 --> 01:16:04,980
Just march yourself yonder
to your horse, mister!

888
01:16:08,180 --> 01:16:09,860
March, mister!
I'm not foolin'!

889
01:16:13,340 --> 01:16:18,060
All right, but you haven't heard
the last of Harry Powell yet.

890
01:16:18,180 --> 01:16:21,340
The Lord God Jehovah will guide
my hand in vengeance!

891
01:16:23,020 --> 01:16:24,860
You devils!

892
01:16:26,340 --> 01:16:28,140
You whores of Babylon!

893
01:16:34,100 --> 01:16:36,500
I'll be back when it's dark.

894
