The Everlasting Arms

912
01:18:06,940 --> 01:18:11,220
Shame on you, Ruby, mooning around
the house after that mad dog of a man.

913
01:18:12,780 --> 01:18:14,900
Merciful heavens!

914
01:18:15,780 --> 01:18:18,660
Ruby, go get the children out of bed
and bring them down here.

915
01:18:21,420 --> 01:18:23,660
Women is such durn fools.

916
01:18:41,740 --> 01:18:44,500
It's a hard world for little things.

917
01:19:04,860 --> 01:19:08,780
Now, there was this sneaking
no-account, ornery King Herod.

918
01:19:08,900 --> 01:19:11,500
And when he heard tell of
little Jesus growin' up, he figured...

919
01:19:11,580 --> 01:19:14,660
"Well, shoot. There won't be
no room for the both of us.

920
01:19:14,740 --> 01:19:16,580
I'll just nip this in the bud."

921
01:19:16,660 --> 01:19:19,900
But he wasn't sure which of all those
babies in the land was King Jesus.

922
01:19:19,980 --> 01:19:22,380
So that cruel old
King Herod figured...

923
01:19:22,500 --> 01:19:26,020
if he killed all the babies in the land,
he'd be sure and get little Jesus.

924
01:19:26,100 --> 01:19:29,060
And when little King Jesus' ma and pa
heard about this plan...

925
01:19:29,180 --> 01:19:31,780
- what do you reckon they went and done?
- They hid in a broom closet.

926
01:19:31,860 --> 01:19:35,700
- They hid under the porch.
- No. They went a-runnin'.

927
01:19:35,820 --> 01:19:39,460
Well, now, John, you're right.
That's just what they done.

928
01:19:39,540 --> 01:19:41,900
Little King Jesus' ma and pa
saddled a mule...

929
01:19:42,020 --> 01:19:44,380
and they rode all the way down
into Egypt-land.

930
01:19:44,460 --> 01:19:47,660
Yeah. And that's where the queen
found them in the billy rushes.

931
01:19:47,780 --> 01:19:50,820
Oh, no. That wasn't the same story
at all. That was little King Moses.

932
01:19:50,900 --> 01:19:54,580
But just the same, it did seem like
it was plague time for little ones.

933
01:19:54,700 --> 01:19:57,540
Them olden days.
Them hard, hard times.

934
01:20:04,180 --> 01:20:06,060
Figured I was gone, huh?

935
01:20:06,140 --> 01:20:08,940
Run! Hide in the staircase!
Run quick!

936
01:20:09,020 --> 01:20:11,260
Ruby, get!

937
01:20:11,340 --> 01:20:14,260
- What do you want?
- I want them kids.

938
01:20:14,380 --> 01:20:17,340
- What do you want them for?
- That's none of your business, madam.

939
01:20:17,420 --> 01:20:20,420
I'm givin' you till the count of three
to get out of here, then I'm shootin'!

940
01:20:35,700 --> 01:20:37,820
Miss Booher? Rachel Cooper.

941
01:20:37,900 --> 01:20:39,940
Get your state troopers
out to my place.

942
01:20:40,020 --> 01:20:42,420
I got something trapped
in my barn.

943
01:20:52,540 --> 01:20:55,460
- I'll go see to Pearl.
- I'll make coff ee.

944
01:21:04,820 --> 01:21:06,660
She's all right.

945
01:21:08,740 --> 01:21:10,900
John, you know, when you're little,
you have more endurance...

946
01:21:11,020 --> 01:21:13,500
than God is ever
to grant you again?

947
01:21:13,580 --> 01:21:16,500
Children are man at his strongest.
They abide.

948
01:21:30,540 --> 01:21:33,140
- Why didn't you call us before now?
- Didn't want your dirty shoes...

949
01:21:33,260 --> 01:21:35,420
- trackin' up my clean floors.
- Is that him, ma'am?

950
01:21:35,500 --> 01:21:38,220
Yes. Mind where you shoot, boys.
There are children here.

951
01:21:38,340 --> 01:21:41,900
Harry Powell, you're under arrest
for the murder of Willa Harper.

952
01:21:43,980 --> 01:21:45,260
Drop that knif e.

953
01:21:47,660 --> 01:21:48,500
Don't!

954
01:21:54,460 --> 01:21:56,860
Here, here, take it back!

955
01:21:56,940 --> 01:22:00,580
Take it back! I don't want it, Dad!
It's too much!

956
01:22:00,660 --> 01:22:01,900
Here!

957
01:22:12,220 --> 01:22:14,860
Lynch him!

958
01:22:14,980 --> 01:22:17,740
- Bluebeard!
- Twenty-five wives!

959
01:22:17,860 --> 01:22:19,540
And he killed them all!

960
01:22:19,660 --> 01:22:22,500
- If the people of Marshall County--
- Bluebeard!

961
01:22:28,900 --> 01:22:31,180
Will you identify the prisoner?

962
01:22:31,300 --> 01:22:35,140
Please, little lad, won't you look
yonder and tell the court...

963
01:22:35,260 --> 01:22:37,700
if that is the man
that killed your mother?

964
01:22:44,780 --> 01:22:48,420
It's all right, Mrs. Cooper.
You can take the little f ellow away.

965
01:22:48,500 --> 01:22:50,740
Merry Christmas to you and yours,
Mrs. Cooper.

966
01:22:50,860 --> 01:22:53,820
And what's Santa Claus going to bring
you for Christmas, little man?

967
01:22:54,900 --> 01:22:56,620
Bluebeard!

968
01:23:05,220 --> 01:23:07,940
- There's Pearl!
- Get your coats.

969
01:23:08,020 --> 01:23:10,020
Them's her orphans!

970
01:23:10,100 --> 01:23:11,660
- Where's Ruby?
- She went.

971
01:23:11,780 --> 01:23:14,500
Them poor little lambs!

972
01:23:14,580 --> 01:23:18,540
Them is the ones
he sinned against, my friends!

973
01:23:18,660 --> 01:23:20,460
Go out the back door!

974
01:23:24,340 --> 01:23:26,780
Ain't we goin' to the bus depot?

975
01:23:28,140 --> 01:23:31,460
Draggin' the name of the Lord
through the evil mud of his soul!

976
01:23:31,540 --> 01:23:35,580
- String that Bluebeard up to a post!
- He's Satan hiding behind the cross!

977
01:23:35,660 --> 01:23:37,380
Come on!

978
01:24:20,620 --> 01:24:23,940
I love him.
You think he's like them others.

979
01:24:29,740 --> 01:24:31,740
You were so mad, you shot him!

980
01:24:47,260 --> 01:24:48,740
- Hey, Bart.
- Yeah?

981
01:24:48,820 --> 01:24:52,460
- We're savin' this bird up for you.
- This time it'll be a privilege.

982
01:25:17,340 --> 01:25:19,980
I'm glad they didn't send me nothin'.
Whenever they do, it's nothin' I want...

983
01:25:20,100 --> 01:25:23,620
but just somethin' to show me how fancy
and smart they've come up in the world.

984
01:25:30,100 --> 01:25:32,780
- Can we give you your presents now?
- Shoot.

985
01:25:32,860 --> 01:25:35,340
You don't mean to say
you got me a present.

986
01:25:35,460 --> 01:25:36,940
Shoot, now.

987
01:25:44,940 --> 01:25:46,980
A potholder.

988
01:25:47,100 --> 01:25:49,900
And it's much neater
than last year, Ruby.

989
01:25:53,260 --> 01:25:55,220
Another potholder!

990
01:25:55,340 --> 01:25:58,580
Now, ain't that thoughtful.
I'm always burning my hands.

991
01:26:00,700 --> 01:26:03,420
This doesn't look basted.
This looks made!

992
01:26:04,460 --> 01:26:06,980
And you finished the edge
with a chain-stitch.

993
01:26:07,060 --> 01:26:09,100
Oh, that's just dandy, Clary.

994
01:26:11,820 --> 01:26:13,620
Another potholder?

995
01:26:18,700 --> 01:26:21,420
Oh, now, did you two
make this together?

996
01:26:21,500 --> 01:26:22,980
You helped us some.

997
01:26:31,860 --> 01:26:34,740
That's the richest gift
a body could have.

998
01:26:35,820 --> 01:26:39,460
And your presents are in the cupboard
under the china closet.

999
01:26:44,380 --> 01:26:46,220
This is yours.

1000
01:27:01,500 --> 01:27:04,060
Lord, save little children.

1001
01:27:04,140 --> 01:27:07,140
You'd think the world would be ashamed
to name such a day as Christmas...

1002
01:27:07,220 --> 01:27:10,100
for one of them and then go on
in the same old way.

1003
01:27:11,460 --> 01:27:15,780
My soul is humbled when I see the way
little ones accept their lot.

1004
01:27:17,100 --> 01:27:19,180
Lord, save little children.

1005
01:27:19,300 --> 01:27:22,340
The wind blows,
and the rains are cold.

1006
01:27:22,420 --> 01:27:24,140
Yet they abide.

1007
01:27:51,660 --> 01:27:53,780
That watch is sure
a fine, loud ticker.

1008
01:27:55,660 --> 01:27:59,060
Be nice to have someone around the house
who can give me the right time of day.

1009
01:28:00,300 --> 01:28:03,380
This watch is the nicest watch
I ever had.

1010
01:28:03,500 --> 01:28:07,180
Well, a fellow can't just go around
with run-down, busted watches.

1011
01:28:13,700 --> 01:28:16,100
They abide and they endure.


